POLOKWANE - Opposition parties the DA, EFF, UDM and Cope will take to the streets on Tuesday, this time leading a march to the Limpopo Provincial Treasury. This latest protest is aimed at addressing state capture.READ: Opposition parties to march in Limpopo against state captureIn a statement released on Monday, the DA accuses the ANC of normalising the abuse of citizens' money and institutions for self-benefit.The party says Limpopo is the best case study of state capture, describing the province as economically stagnant and corrupted to the point of near bankruptcy.Tuesday's march follows national demonstrations by the public and opposition parties over the past two weeks, calling for President Jacob Zuma to step down.Tweets about #DAMarch AND(FROM:@ThulasSims since:2017-04-18) eNCA